There is currently no universally accepted process for naming  clades and reconciling them with the traditional taxonomic  categories of the International Code of Nomenclature for Algae,  Fungi and Plants (ICNAFP), although the draft PhyloCode   (http://www.ohio.edu/phylocode/) represents a major step in this direction.

In response to these historic changes, the International  Subcommission on Colletotrichum  Taxonomy has been set up  within the framework of the International Commission on the  Taxonomy of Fungi (http://www.fungaltaxonomy.org/).
